caption: Great food and amazing people running it. Definitely stop in! Had the jugoslavijan sausage spring rolls, the beef pho and their vegetarian lemongrass pho. Incredible flavors! Owner was very friendly and a joy to talk to. Will be coming back to try the sandwich!
Came here with my girlfriend for a dinner, food was awesome, owner was very nice and funny, we tried different brandy’s together with him! Will definitely come back!

I ordered their vegan stir fry (has to be requested vegan) and it’s so flavorful. On top of that it’s very fulfilling and satiating! This place is amazing. Great neighborhood feel! The owners are two of the most genuine, realest people you could meet, and their service is top notch. They’re very accommodating, and you can expect the owner to offer you a shot of brandy for free if you go in to pick-up your food! Pls support this business! Try it out and tell a friend !
The Banh Xeo (Vietnamese pancake) is even better than my Ba Noi’s (grandma’s)! Small selection of excellent dishes and soups- expect fresh herbs, spicy sauces, and super friendly owner.
Wow was blown away.  The spicy lemongrass soup is a must have, definitely coming back!
Pho is amazing ! Owners are so friendly,  feels like at home
Incredible food, beautiful family!
Excellent food, large portions, great service. Ordered take out and got to try some brandy while I waited. The pho was exactly what I was looking for on a cold winter night.
Delicious

Absolutely incredible food! By far, the best pho I have had in my entire life and the ambience at the restaurant is wonderful. They do a great job ensuring everyone is comfortable and safe with COVID protocols. The owners make everyone feel so welcome and the Croatian food is phenomenal as well. Can't wait to come back soon!
My fav location for quality vietnamese food. Visited near twelve, it was not full. Had a friend come into town and she asked me to take her here again. The place has a great feel to it.
Fantastic

Ordered the lemongrass soup, chicken pho, spring rolls, egg rolls and calamari- broth was quite bland, lemongrass soup wasn’t spicy, the egg rolls had an odd after taste. Calamari was okay and the spring rolls were good! Genuinely surprised given the reviews. Will try again another time
Great food. Great people. Great location. Great prices. Great experience. Sunset Pho is a gem!

A Coworker recommended this place to me recently and my fiance and I just tried it tonight for the first time.  Beef Salad was awesome and had all the best flavors. Beef Pho was the best pho I've had in the city. Pork Bahn Mi was great too. Great meal for the 2 of us!
Got delivery, it was very tasty and well packaged!
vietnamese food and service at this location is excellent. the staff was sociable and attentive.
Best pho around for sure. I used to work there and can attest they make a lot of items from scratch.

UPDATE: Just ordered takeout and WOW - fell in love all over again. It is SO nice to find good pho in Lincoln Park and not have to drive all the way to Argyle. Everything was package so nicely in terms of carry out and I am in a total food coma. Still recommend the ginger chicken cabbage salad and seafood pho - seafood was cooked perfectly.  Loved the ginger chicken cabbage salad!! Also had seafood pho which was excellent! Can’t wait to go back!

Just left this restaurant and cannot say enough great things! They are taking great precaution in terms of the pandemic. And beyond that the food was amazing! We had the vegetarian pho, pan fried noodles, and fried rice. Everything was light and flavorful, hands down now my favorite spot. Zel and Nok (husband wife owners) were so welcoming, we stayed late and hung out at the bar drinking and trying new Yugoslavian concoctions. Better service than some of the Michelin Star restaurants that I’ve been to. I’m already planning on ordering in from them tomorrow!
Really great mom and pop shop. The food was amazing and the service was authentic. We had to ask to order and for the the check, but really great!
Really loved the chicken Pho!

Excellent food, excellent service! Zeli and his lovely wife are awesome, they take great care of the customers. The fusion of Vietnamese and Eastern European food is unique and very tasty. Very respectful of masks and social distancing.

My husband and I were starving and could not find any restaurants open in the area. This is the only place we found that allowed dine in. Walking into this place felt like a magical experience. Everything from the lights on the wall to the stained glass windows, it was all so beautiful ! Please if your in the area do yourself a favor and eat here! The food is amazing!!! I can't say enough good things about this place. Excellent service, excellent everything. One of a kind top notch experience!
Delicious food and very friendly atmosphere
The chicken pho was phenomenal! Will be getting it again!
Ok spot for quality Vietnamese food. Great location to meet with friends. Next time I'll be back with my friends. The bill was good for how much you get.
Vietnamese food, super good. super place to meet and chat with coworkers. the service was very kind and attentive. ambience is similar to fresno's scene.
Vietnamese food, mmm, awesome. Visited Fri evening I think.

What a phenomenal and unique combination: Vietnamese and Yugoslavian cuisine. I even forgot there was a pandemic happening around us because I was experiencing such a lovely dining experience. Great customer service and tasty, legit food. Highly recommend.

Our new favorite Pho spot! Zell and his wife are amazing hosts serving some of the best Pho in the city. I highly recommend the Cevapcici (goi cuon) spring roll and any one of the large selection of fruit infused Brandy (which the owner adds himself). If you have the chance, you must check out this cozy and unique restaurant.

The best pho I’ve ever had! (I had the rare angus beef and my partner had the brisket, both excellent!) Pork egg rolls were also amazing. You could taste the love and care that went into the food. Owners were so nice and personable and gave great recommendations. Prices were very fair given the quality and amount of food we received. We will definitely be back!
Good scene for tasty vietnamese food. Service is always timely even when they have a full house. Service treated us so kindly. Prices are reasonable I would say.

I just tried this place for the first time even though I live right down the street and I regret not trying it sooner. We got the vegetarian stir fried wide noodles and the beef noodle salad and both were great!!! Most delicious food around I’ve had in a while. I will definitely be back and look forward to start dining in when they open up completely because it looks quite cozy inside.

This place is awesome! Owner is a super nice guy, poured me a shot of the good stuff while I was waiting on my Pho that his wife crafts in the back. The meal was great and they even accommodated my girlfriend’s vegetarian diet. Would really like to come back in here and hang out when COVID blows over! Cheers!
Vietnamese food, super delicious. The prices are fair for the quality of food. Menu is similar to a restaurant in El Paso I liked.
vietnamese food and the setting at this location is excellent. Came here on a Saturday. I will be back with my friends. The place has an awesome atmosphere.
vietnamese food at this spot - delicious. Looking forward to a return trip. The prices are fair for the quality of food.
One of my fav spots for Vietnamese food. I love this place, excellent food & service. Staff treated us so kindly.

This place is amazing and has EXCELLENT service. I ordered through UberEats and they took a long time (their fault) so I called the restaurant directly. The owner, Zel, answered the phone and proceeded to offer to deliver my order himself because the service had not picked it up. These types of experiences are what makes a place worth going back. I will be going out of my way to pick up from this restaurant directly and not through delivery apps in the future. 15/10 service. Thanks so much!

Amazing lil spot! My husband and I met the owner while we waited for our food and he’s great guy- him and his wife run the place. We ordered the pork banh mi and beef brisket pho- both were so tasty. They bake the bread for the banh mi fresh, which made it even more yummy. They’re only doing takeout right now, but excited for them to open for dining soon!

I was traveling through Chicago and found this place to stop at for a few hours' reprise- and what a treat it was! The food is absolutely incredible! Sunset Pho is a super fun fusion restaurant which combines perfectly classic Vietnamese foods with a little interesting Slavic influence mixed in on some menu items (like the veal spring rolls and the plum brandy- both so delicious!) you will not be disappointed eating here. I'm looking forward to the next time I am in Chicago so I can stop by and chat with the owner, Zal, again and eat their impeccably good food!
Great quality Vietnamese and great new location. Owners are ideal mom and pop. Chicken quality and tender, lemongrass sauce is perfect and not artificial. Very authentic and quality!!!
Friendly owner, good food, and good sized portions for the price. Will be going back to try more.
Guy b okn
The best pho and great people!
Came for happy hour and the house wine was wonderful! Great atmosphere and our waitress Stephanie was the BEST. Will definitely be back
Awesome food and friendly ownership. Order and keep this wonderful place alive!

I’m a pho addict and can honestly say this is the best pho I’ve had outside of Vietnam. (I even got a pho tattoo to show off my addiction). My partner and I always order the chicken pho with rice noodles and spicy lemongrass broth. Highly suggest you check this local place out for your next comfort food kick. 10 out of 10!!

An honest business that serves honestly good food! From north to south, Sunset Pho serves the best pho in Chicago! The owners are always working to make sure that the food is perfect, and are so friendly! They fill a dire need in the neighborhood, and are a weekly staple for me. Definitely recommend!

The service and food were amazing! I ordered the Mantissa Curry and the meat was so tender. The curry sauce was amazing and the rice was cooked to perfection. 100% would recommend, especially because the service was so great!

I brought my Uncle and Aunt here to get some drinks and a small bite before the show. We got dumplings, spring rolls and spare ribs on the sugarcane. We were really impressed by the presentations and flavors and the service! Everyone enjoyed everything. It was a good choice.

Phenomenal Pho. Everything from the broth, to the noodles, and all of the toppings were delicious. Additionally, the service here is top notch—both quick and very personable. Don’t miss this hidden gem, it’s absolutely worth ordering-in or ordering to-go!

What a great place and fun restaurant in East Lakeview (2 block from Landmark Century Centre Cinema). Vietnamese and Jugoslavian fusion serving the Best Pho soup and some Balkan specialty like cheese and potato pie (Burek), homemade bread rolls with CHEVAPS  (minced meat sausages), and CHEVAPS in spring rolls. The owners are super friendly!Želimir Is welcoming and when we are ready to leave, he walks us to the door...we feel like we are a family. They have full bar and fun cocktails. I highly recommend Sunset Pho 🙂
Nice Pho!
Great food and the staff are extremely friendly
Got the chicken Pho and it was delicious. You can expect a quality Vietnamese meal if you eat here.
Great food, even better staff, and well priced. What are you waiting for?

My girlfriend and I enjoyed Valentine's Day 2020 here and it was perfect. The food was delicious! The menu is a mix of Vietnamese food with a European bar. Best Pho we've eaten in Chicago. The owners are very sweet and generous, plus every woman got a rose.
The food was delicious. The owner was very pleasant and homely to talk to. The service was great and seems personal. The only complaint would be that the food came out fairly slow.
The brisket Pho was delicious! Amazing brandy from the owners home country, great service and hospitality!!! Cant wait to go back !
Amazing food and service!
Awesome, loved it, went back on two additional opportunities.
Wonderful service and kind staff. Got the pork belly sandwhich and the special pho and they were both very delicious!

The pho was ok, but the pork belly sandwiches/banh mi were atrocious. Not only was is not at all delicious (the pork belly was gamy and rubbery, the vegetables were not pickled or crunchy), but it gave my sister food poisoning.
Great food! Vegetarian and vegan friendly too!
Great food for vegans! I liked the vegetarian pho and the wide rice noodles with tofu. The atmosphere was good for a date or a conversation with friends.

New to the neighborhood and have been searching for good Pho in Lincoln Park. THIS IS IT! The owner was super friendly and hospitable, he treated us to a free drink from his home country of Yugoslavia. His wife is Vietnamese and makes the outstanding food. Highly recommend and will be going back!
The best Chicken Pho in Chicago. The Owner is hilarious and deserves a round of applause.

The pho was delicious. My wife and I had a wonderful date night dinner. Staff is very friendly and welcoming. The owner actually came out and had a birthday shot with us and brang out a delicious desert on the house. My salmon in fish sauce was amazing. I highly recommend this place! The atmosphere is perfect....
I loved the food. The staff was nice. The pho was simply delicious.
Great food and amazing service!
Great location and amazing food. Loved the veggie pho!
Really great food!
Fantastic place.  Wonderful owners,  incredibly helpful and charming bartender.   A hidden gem on north Clark street.  I highly recommend this restaurant!!!
The Pho was great! The service was under par. Very sweet space so Im sure I will be back to give it another try. I just hope the second time is the charm.
Interesting Eastern Euro vibe, due to the interracial couple running the place... EE and Vietnamese... support a local SBO. Decent food, iffy service.

Officially one of my most favorite restaurants ever! The staff was super friendly, the pho was delicious with generous proportions (especially for a take out order), fresh ingredients. You Must give this place a try.
Delicious broth of the pho.  It was meaty the portion was generous.
Great pho! Great prices! Staff very friendly!
Great food, great service!
Great Pho, even to go
Good food, cool atmos.

OUTSTANDING Vietnamese food. I had  pan fried noodles with seafood (tons of calamari and mussells and shrimp), companion had pho, both were so aromatic and delicious! Now at their new location on Clark and better than ever.
Delicious food, reasonably priced, very friendly staff!! highly recommend
Always excellent at Sunset Oho Cafe
Great food, friendly ownership, unique cuisine. Highly recommended!
Flavorful veggie pho!
Delicious pho and great Croatian wines! Everyone was kind and hospitable!

Best restaurant I've ever eaten at. The owner is such a great man, so hospitable. Took care of us the entire night. FOOD IS HANDS DOWN THE MOST DELICIOUS IVE EVER EATEN, vietnamese or not. YOU NEED TO GO TO THIS PLACE RIGHT NOW !! For breakfast, lunch, dinner, snack. every meal go here

We stopped in at Sunset Pho after walking past it on our way home, and we were not disappointed. The Cevepcic (Jugoslavian Sausage) Spring Rolls were amazing! We both got the Beef Pho with the Rare Angus Beef, and it was also delicious. The personal touch by the restaurant owners made the experience even more special. We learned how a Jugoslavian / Vietnamese restaurant came to be (a love story :) ) and even was offered some traditional Jugoslavian spirit! A great date night place that doesn't break the bank! Must Try!!!

Really good food and really nice restaurateurs! The Beef Pho was delicious, really nice balance of yummy flavors! The ingredients were top notch and well packed (mine was a pick up order) and the portion size was on point.

This place has amazing food. The service is also very good. While waiting for our carryout, the owner gave us water and told us a little bit about the establishment. The food was fresh and tasted better than other vietnamese places. I recommend this restaurant.
Best Pho in Chicago. Hands Sown!
unique blend of Slavic and Vietnamese flavors

Delicious! This is an amazing spot to have dinner that has traditional and fusion foods. This restaurant is a fusion of Vietnamese and Yugoslavian cuisine.  They have a cevapcici fresh spring roll! If you're not familiar with cevapcici then you are missing out. Cevapcici is a sausage like ground meet patty with Yugoslavian spices.  They also have traditional pho and fresh spring rolls if you are not feeling adventurous.  The owner even came by and gave us shots of traditional Yugoslavian brandy and chatted with us about it! Makes you feel welcomed and at home!  Can not wait to go back to try more items from their menu!
A must-try fusion between Vietnamese and Yugoslavian cuisine with generous portions. Owners and staff are incredibly friendly!
Outstanding food and friendly service.
So friendly and so delicious! The N Clark new location is super cute. Pho soup club FTW!!
Amazing service, food, and ambiance! Will definitely be back. Get the Vietnamese crepe and alllllll the pho!
One of the best pho spots in the city! The broth is hands down the best I’ve had. Also love the Serbian take on the spring rolls - definitely a must try.
What an amazing experience. The food is 10/10 and the service and people running the restaurant are even greater. A very homey and welcoming vibe. You won’t be disappointed !

I come from VA,DC,MD area, one of the best areas for Vietnamese food. My review here is based on that scale.  First impression is the interior design is charming. It is more European than Vietnamese. I was greeted by a European man who continued  to be the server too. He acted like he's a friendly owner of a family restaurant.  I ordered beef meatball phở and egg rolls. The egg rolls themselves are good, just like what I expected. However, they weren't served with authentic nước chấm, but with Thai sweet chili sauce. Not a complaint, but wish otherwise. Phở is always judged by its broth. This broth is good; clear, flavorful, natural. The noodle was a bit too thin and few. The meatballs were typical, up to standard. The condiments were lacking. Bean sprouts were short and discolored. I wish there was more green onions. 4 stars because up to my standard. Not 5 star because did not wow me. Will come back if convenient. Will not go out of way.

While visiting Chicago I was happy to find the Sunset Pho near my hotel, vietnamese soups are my favorite meals. And the owners are very hospitable and wonderful, they offered me to taste a plum brandy from Croatia, which was very good. I would definitely visit them again.
Super fresh food great service! Nice menu options. You can go from heavy meaty to light and fresh depending on your mood. A neighborhood treasure.
Cozy spot. Great Pho and spring rolls. Staff is very friendly.

This is an interesting combo of Vietnamese and Slavic.Love the decor and friendly service. The pho was flavorful and accompanied by the freshest sprouts and basil. The rice paper spring roll with smoked sausage was delicious. Got a free shot of Apricot brandy for complimenting the great selection of music.

Best pho in Chicago, not kidding. Get the chicken pho every time and it’s incredible. Also order the sausage spring rolls, don’t ask questions. Great wine selection as well. The waiters are always helpful and recommend the best dishes for the night. Can not recommend this place more!
Delicious rolls and pho!!!! Best in Chicago

Visiting from Hawaiʻi, and was in dire need of some good Pho!  And this place didn’t disappoint!  Such good food.  Great ambience.  And the owners were so nice and welcoming.  Amazing amazing amazing!  Aloha from Hawaiʻi <3
Amazing I love both locations even though the new one is further away it is still worth going too.
Had their Beef Pho and it was so good. The owner and staff are extremely nice. The ambiance is charming -perfect for a romantic date night.
Beautiful place with tasty food! Dennis was very attentive and, overall, we had good time! We are definitely coming back!
Awesome people, amazing food, and tasty liquor!!! Clean, friendly, definitely visiting again!!
Great Pho! Nice owners.
The spring rolls use Yugoslavian meat. The Pho was amazing. A mix of Vietnam and Yugoslavian recipes.
Family owned and operated, welcoming atmosphere, and most importantly delicious Pho! Worth a visit!

It's basically good Vietnamese food but with some Yugoslavia and Serbian twists. The quality of everything was excellent. The flavors are maybe a little stronger than traditional Vietnamese fare, but overall an excellent t experience and delicious food. Owner is extremely friendly.
You must try their scallops😋
Food was great and the service was amazing, server was helpful, answered our questions and made great food and wine suggestions.

This saves you a visit to uptown if you live in the LP area. We tried the rice noodle dish with sausage which was an interesting take on the dish but was delish. This was a great helping for a reasonable price. There weren’t many ppl in when we came as it was off peak hours but service was great. Need to come back for pho

Loved it! Me and my wife traveled to Vietnam a year ago, and all the food from the Caffe tastes anf fills authentic and delicious. I loved extra fusion on few dishes that combines both owners' diverse background. The service was amazing an overall a 5 star experience. Great job, would definitely come again many times.
Best pho in the city.  Hands down.
Pho broth is out of this world! Highly recommend

We absolutely love this place! It keeps getting better every time we come back for more!! Their menu is amazing! Our goto's are the  lemongrass soup (soooooo goood), and their trademark Sunset special Pho... also because one of the owners is yugoslavian, they offer some very cool twists on your regular vietnamese cuisine. Try the spring rolls with the cevapcici (yugoslavian sausage). The owners/staff is truly amazing. Easily the best service we have experienced in quite some time. From the moment you walk through the door, you feel like family and are welcomed into their home ❤

Quiet place with a nice atmosphere. The food was great, the mix of Vietnamese and Jugoslavian food seems like an odd mix but it all tasted great. I ordered a beef lemongrass sandwich and the bread is made per order so it was amazing. I tried some of the Pho and it is a lot for one person but it tasted great.

The food is very authentic. The phơ hits all the right notes, with a clean, savory and satisfying finish. I also tried their grilled pork bánh mì and the picked vegetables complemented the rich paté nicely. Definitely lived up to my standards as a Vietnamese person. The cevapcici spring rolls were great too!
If you're on the fence about this place because you don't know what a  Yugoslavian/Vietnamese restaurant is like, do your self a favor and go for it, it's just really good food.
Great atmosphere.  The Yugoslavian sausage dishes are very good. Recommend Noodle Salad with the sausage!

Sunset pho was a pretty pleasant dining experience! Our table got a variety of food including pho, sandwiches, and Mongolian beef. The food was all very good, even the fries, which were of unexpected quality for a location of it's genre. The only downside was that there was one server for the whole place and when it started to get a little busy, he wasnt enough to cover the whole place.
Great vegetarian pho!

What an amazing find.  The interior looks like a German church!  The give out shots of plum brandy.  The owner personally greeted everyone in the restaurant.  I had salmon and it was fresh and light.  We got a bottle of Dalmation coast wine.  So good.  Prices are reasonable.
Friendly staff and delicious food!

I loved this place so much I went back the next day. The beef pho is delicious. I also tried a few of the appetizers and have loved everything. Owner is very friendly and welcoming. Can't wait to go back.
(Translated by Google) They should try their specialties.  (Original) Treba probati njihove specijalitete..Veliki pozdrav za Vlasnika Želimira...
Phenomenal food. Amazing pho and shaken beef.
Delicious and authentic with friendly service. Very interment setting with a great bar selection as well. So glad we found this place. Our new go to for Vietnamese!!!
Awesome,fresh food! My shrimp noodle salad was delicious! From Rochester NY. Can't wait to visit Chicago just to eat here.
Best. Pho. Ever. Hands down. The owner is incredible, he and his wife spend 11 hours making the broth!!! All the goodness you will ever need.
Very delicious and quirky place. I went there with 3 other friends and it took a while for us to get our food, but the wait time was worth it. Pho has a very nice flavor and the portions are huge!
Delicious food! The owners are so welcoming and hospitable! We had the rare beef pho, rice platter, and spring rolls with their own twist! Definitely coming back!
I love this place
(Translated by Google) Very good service, exquisite food, would be safe. Very nice neighborhood  (Original) Molt bon servei, menjar exquisit, tornaria segur. Barri molt agradable
Absolutely delicious food and amazing service. The owner is very proud of his food and it shows. Amazing. Will be back.
Service and food are excellent. Extremely conveniently located.

Had the chance to talk to Zel before, during, and after dinner with my pals. Service was great, and the food was a 10/10.  The menu is Vietnamese and Yugoslavian, and I highly doubt you will find anything similar anywhere else! Try any of the Vietnamese dishes with the Cevapcici (traditional Yugoslavian sausages). If you're not sure what to get, the staff will be more than happy to advise you :').
Excellent noodles - great services

Most wonderful restaurant we visited in a while. We were greeted by friendly staff and shown to the window table right away. Our trip started with RAKIJA ŠLJIVOVICA and PELINKOVAC (cure for everything). Overwhelmed by the choices from Yugoslavia and Vietnam in the middle of the day we decided to take it easy and come back for everything else we can't eat now. GURMANSKA PLJESKAVICA and SPICY LEMONGRASS SOUP made the cut for the first round. Everything else will just have to wait. While we waited we had more rakija and pelinkovac, some water as well. Lemongrass soup came first. Half a minute before pljeskavica. Just enough for both of us to try it and understand that the choice we made was right. It was everything I wanted and more. 12 hour broth is recognizable right away. Perfectly spiced it just makes you savor every spoon you put in your mouth. Amazing. More rakija. More pelinkovac. Time to switch. Just by looking at the texture I could tell it was going to be great and it was. If you don't know what pljeskavica is and you like burgers this is it only much better. Don't skip the onions that come with it. It's part of the dish. You can't eat one without the other. Same goes for ćevapčić dish. Liberating experience of onion smell and not a care in the world for a few moments.  Rakija might've played a role in it as well. We're coming back for more of the same and different. Loved everything about it. Experience,  food, atmosphere, location...  Everything.
Amazing fusion of Yugoslavian and Vietnamese food

A fusion between Vietnamese and Yugoslavian cuisine run by a couple from both places.The pho with Yugoslavian sausage is so yummy. The atmosphere is funky and is like a cave(?). Definitely go if you like pho.

Treat you like family is an abused phrase in the review world, but it honestly is true at Sunset Pho Caffe. The owners take pride in the menu and treat guests like the restaurant was an extension of their home. No doubt Chicago is filled to the brim with overrated eateries that are well decorated (with a price tag to match) but lack heart and soul. When everything from the reclaimed wood floors to the "vintage" signs to the grammable quotes on the wall is calculated by an expensive designer to evoke certain reactions, you feel like a kid in an amusement park full of mechanical smiles and rehearsed personas. Tipping culture and competition is probably to blame, but regardless authenticity gets lost, including in the food. As for the Sunset pho tai, it's the best one I've had in Chicago. There I said it. The broth is, just as Zel described, "rich but not heavy". Everything is made from scratch - the broth has so much flavor crammed into every cubic inch, each spoonful solicits another and another. The deliciousness is no surprise - it cooks for over 10 hours! A telltale color of good pho broth is light tan, not dark brown. Ever since we came back from a trip to Hanoi, Vietnam we wondered why US-ified, Americanized pho was so greasy and intense when the real thing is actually quite clean and light. As much as I love soup and brothy things, I could never have much before I felt too full and sleepy and had to take the rest home. This was the first time I almost finished the entire bowl. Even the fiance was impressed. Credit goes to him for finding this gem! Like most wonderful things, it was an accidental discovery since our usual place on Argyle was closed Mondays. I'll be enthusiastically recommending it from now on as a remedy for American pho and the hype restaurants, especially if you appreciate charming interiors and an old-time feel where a writer may be huddled over their notebook at a corner table, bathed in the glow of a warm lamp and a scotch (or in this case, plum brandy!). Somewhere between Europe and Asia, but not on any map.
Service is great, food is good but price is steep, compared to what a cost of a sandwich should be. People in Houston would expect 2 or 3 sandwiches for the price of one here.

This is a must stop if you love great food. You walk in and realize right away the place is a gem. It is a very relaxed and beautifully space. There is a little tavern hidden in the restaurant where you can pull up a high chair and have a drink. Then there is the food! Maybe the best vietnamese I have ever had. Dishes are delicious and very large portions. We had pho soup, rice, an egg noodle dish and we could not stop eating. Our 13, 11, and 8 year old girls loved the food.  The owners offer a unique blend of veitnamese and Jugoslavian and are super friendly. We had a unique Croatian/Yukoslavian beer that was so refreshing with our meal on the advice of the owner. We spent 14 days in Chicago before heading back to Canada and this was our best meal and we had some really good food!  Could not rate this place high enough.
Really Great vegan options - loved the vegan pho. The owners are very nice and accommodating. I'm going next time in in the neighborhood!

The rare beef Pho was great and so close to my home in Lincoln Park. Usually I have to go to Uptown to get good Pho. They gave me a ton of meat and noodles and the broth was magical. The restaurant itself boasts a blending of yugoslavian and vietnamese food. Im sure some dishes are hybrids but they also hold true to traditional methods of various dishes. The one major change in my Pho was that it came with cracked black pepper in it. It had just enough kick that i didnt need sriracha or anything else. The service was good too.
Great food and great customer service.
Amazing vegetarian pho! My friend liked his chicken pho as well. Great prices, calm cool relaxing atmosphere with good music, and very hospitable service. I highly recommend.
I had the cevapcici and it was delicious.  Owners and staff are very nice and accommodating.  Will definitely be going back to try other items.
Interesting may be moving.

Had an amazing dinner date at Sunset Pho Cafe. The staff are extremely kind and welcoming. We were greeted at the door and taken care throughout our meal. The food definitely leads, delicious flavors and presentation. Will definitely come back to hangout at the bar, great vibes!

Had an amazing dinner date at Sunset Pho Cafe. The staff are extremely kind and welcoming. We were greeted at the door and taken care throughout our meal. The food definitely leads, delicious flavors and presentation. Will definitely come back to hangout at the bar, great vibes!

The Pho was delicious!! Order a seafood Pho. The people that own this place are so sweet and welcoming!! We order a Lemon Drop and Sex on the beach,Omg the drinks were so good!  Would definitely come back!

The combination between Yugoslavian and Vietnamese is definitely unique and a true synergy. The flavours are perfectly mixed and the hosts are really welcoming. We had the Vietnamese pie as starter which I would highly recommend. Quality-price is unbalanced, this quality you would pay more. Thumbs up to this newby.
Interesting choice of Vietnamese and Yugoslavian.  Vietnamese was good - vegetarian pho, soft noodles and tofu. Tofu was a ltlle tough, but overall flavors were very good.
Best food i had in years! Everybody's sound eat here, a delicious love story written in food! I really couldn't stop from eating the incredible special sauces.

Fantastic mongolian beef which they made special for me without sugar. Very friendly and accomidating owners paired with a quality meal in a nice relaxed setting made for a great stop. Glad I gave this place a shot and highly recommend it.

Went here on a Sunday afternoon, the place was packed, which is a good indication of great food.  We were intrigued by the combination of Vietnamese and Croatian food, but did not know what to expect.  I asked our waiter for recommendations and he recommended the Cevapcici spring rolls, which is number one under appetizers, and number 45 which is stir-fry chicken or beef with veggies.  We did start off with number 1, because these were the Yugoslavian spring rolls and we also ordered number 2, La's smoked salmon spring rolls to start ($5 for 2 egg rolls)  For our courses we ordered number 18 which is grilled lemongrass pork, shrimp and I will with noodles. It comes with steamed rice noodles, shredded lettuce, bean sprout mint, basil, cucumber pickle, carrot, radish, Ginger, crushed peanuts and their special sauce on the side. We also ordered number 26 which is the rare and flank beef pho soup.  Number 18 is a cold dish, which I feel would be better served on hot summer days, and the pho soup is an excellent choice on colder days. Be careful with the Special Sauce for number 18. Sprinkle a little bit on top first to see how it tastes before adding any additional sauce, as it can get spicy.  Both dishes were delicious,  huge portions, the spring rolls are two large spring rolls which they will cut in half for you. One order spring rolls is more than enough for two people, next time we will only get one order. The cebapcici spring rolls were our favorite, very different and very tasty.  When you enter the restaurant you go past the Long Bar on the left and someone will greet you and seat you, you then step up to the elevated dining area where they have 5 tables for four people one table for two people and three tables that can accommodate 6 people. There is also seating at the long Bar in front, but when we were there no one was eating at the bar.  Did not need reservations on a Sunday afternoon, but they were almost full. I would imagine that you need to make a reservation for weekend evenings.  The menu is very large and there are several interesting items that we want to return for and try.

There are a ton of places to get Pho on Argle, but don't waste your time. My girlfriend and I were coming from Evanston and wanted to try something off that well-trodden path. The night had some very special significance and Sunset Pho did not disappoint. Had no idea of the Vietnamese/Croatian connection as I only saw the star rating and did not read the reviews. What a nice surprise! I've had the cevapcici out at summer festivals and learned that it's made by a relative of the owner. Yes, those spring rolls are as tasty as they sound, and I want more of them. My *very* special dining partner and I both ordered the seafood pho, and we would happily order that dish again as well, tasty broth, fresh ingredients and all the types of seafood cooked just right.  As has been previously mentioned, the owners are a husband and wife team, and Zel came through with some of that wonderful Croatian brandy and conversation to finish our meal and take our evening to a place where wonderful memories live. We also learned from Zel's wife, Ngoc, that they have taken to calling the table we were seated "the Love table" as they seat many first-time daters there. This wasn't our first date, but there was definitely some love shared at that table. Sunset Pho may not be in the greatest location, but we felt the love and the warmth of people who care about their customer's experience. Sretna Nova Godina!
